<refnamediv>
  <refname>lperewr</refname>
  <refpurpose>rewrite data expressions in an LPE</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
  <cmdsynopsis>
    <command>&lperewr;</command>
    <arg choice="plain" rep="repeat"><arg choice="opt">&option;</arg></arg>
    <arg choice="opt">&infile;
    <arg choice="opt">&outfile;</arg>
    </arg>
  </cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1>
  <title>Description</title>
  <para>
    The &lperewr; tool rewrites data expressions occurring in a linear process
    equation (LPE). It reads the LPE from &infile; and writes the result to
    &outfile;. If &outfile; is not present, &stdout; is used. If &infile; is not
    present, &stdin; is used.
  </para>
  <para>
    The following data expressions are rewritten:
    <itemizedlist spacing='compact'>
    <listitem>
      <para>conditions, action parameters, time expressions and next
      states of LPE summands</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>process parameters of the initial state</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>conditions and right-hand sides of data equations</para>
    </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>
  <para>
    Rewriting LPE summands and the initial state is done to simplify these
    parts of the LPE. Rewriting data equations is done to speed up state space
    generation. In most cases, this results in a performance gain of at most 5%.
  </para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>Options</title>
<para>
  <variablelist>
  <varlistentry>
    <term>&opt_h;</term>
    <term>&opt_help;</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        display help message and terminate
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>&opt_version;</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        display version information and terminate
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>&opt_q;</term>
    <term>&opt_quiet;</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        do not display warning messages
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>&opt_v;</term>
    <term>&opt_verbose;</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        display concise intermediate messages
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>&opt_b;</term>
    <term>&opt_benchmark;=&num;</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        rewrite data expressions &num; times; do not save output
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>&opt_r;</term>
    <term>&opt_rewriter;=&name;</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        rewrite data expressions using rewriter &name; (default 'inner')
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</para>
</refsect1>

